Package com.pandora.config.species.abstractions

Interface SpecieLogic

All Known Implementing Classes:
AqueousSpecie, DIC, DOC, SedimentarySpecie, Specie
public interface SpecieLogic
The SpecieLogic interface defines methods for calculating the transport of a biogeochemical species in the freshwater system. Implementing classes should provide concrete implementations for the calculateTransport(double, double) method, which calculates the transport value based on the given amount and discharge parameters. The transport calculation is influenced by the specific logic associated with the behavior of the species in the freshwater system.
Version:
0.0.1
Author:
